- Context: This page outlines the roles and responsibilities within a permit-to-work (PTW) system, covering Permit Issuers, Permit Acceptors, Area Authorities, and Supporting Roles.
- Text: 6. Roles and Responsibilities
Clarity in roles is essential to prevent failure.
6.1 Permit Issuer
•
•
Typically a supervisor or authorised person
Responsibilities:
Ο Verify controls are in place
Ο
Ensure risk assessment is suitable
Ο
Confirm work conditions are safe
6.2 Permit Acceptor (Performer)
•
Person or team carrying out the work
Responsibilities:
Ο Understand the permit and controls
Ο Follow specified conditions
Ο Stop work if conditions change
6.3 Area Authority
Responsible for the operational area
Responsibilities:
0
Authorise work within their area
•
Ensure coordination with other activities
•
Maintain oversight of SIMOPS
6.4 Supporting Roles
•
Isolation authority
Gas tester
•
Safety advisor
