- Context: This page provides a summary of common failure points in Permit-to-Work (PTW) systems. The failures are categorized by area of weakness: over-permitting, poor risk assessment, lack of verification, weak role clarity, breakdown in SIMOPS control, and isolation failures.
- Text: •	Built for the Real World → Usable under operational pressures
•	Clear Communication → Easy to understand and apply

8. Common Failure Points in PTW Systems
8.1 Over-Permitting
o	Too many permits dilute focus
•	Leads to complacency

8.2 Poor Risk Assessment
o	Generic or copied content
o	Failure to identify site-specific hazards

8.3 Lack of Verification
•	Controls assumed, not checked
•	"Sign and go" culture

8.4 Weak Role Clarity
•	Issuers not competent
•	Acceptors not engaged
o	Area authority not actively coordinating

8.5 Breakdown in SIMOPS Control
•	Conflicting work activities
•	Lack of central visibility

8.6 Isolation Failures
o	Incorrect or incomplete isolations
•	No physical verification
